    "body": "As for using `path::SEP` instead of e.g. \"foo/bar\", is there a nice way to do this? The best I've come up with is:\n\n```\n\"foo\".to_string() + SEP.to_string() + \"bar\"\n```\n\nIt's not _horrible_, but seems a bit icky. Alternatively, could I use `join` everywhere instead?\n",
